\b\fs28 Customisation and configuration\par
\b0\fs24 A .slang file (ShieldOfFaith.slang) is used to create the shader that ShaderGlass applies to the screen. You could edit that file, or create multiple, and make different configurations that load different files.\par
An .sgp file (ShieldOfFaith.sgp) is used to set up ShaderGlass with correct settings. By default, Shader glass applies fancy retro-gaming modifications that make it look like you're playing on a TV from 1990. You could edit that file, or create multiple, and make different configurations that load different files.\par
To govern whether or not ShaderGlass.exe darkens the mouse cursor, change the "Capture cursor" setting. For now, that is done by controlling the instructions in the .sgp-file. (CaptureCursor "0" would mean that it leaves the cursor be, CaptureCursor "1" means it will replace the system cursor with a darkened one.)\par
You can also make such adjustments in the Shader Glass app directly at runtime. For easy access to its menus, you would use the window mode button to switch it out of fullscreen.\par
More details on ShaderGlass are presently available at:\par
{{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://mausimus.github.io/ShaderGlass/MANUAL.html }}{\fldrslt{https://mausimus.github.io/ShaderGlass/MANUAL.html\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs24\par
\b\fs28 Customisation and configuration - command line\par
\b0\fs24 Implemented command line options:\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1 --no-deploy (also: -nd): do not create missing configuration files (including sgp and slang files) in the program's %appdata% folder.\b\fs28\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b0\fs24 --data <path to folder> (also: -ad, -d): use a specified folder instead of the program's %appdata% folder. This implicitly adds --no-deploy.\b\fs28\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b0\fs24 --config <path to config file> (also: --settings, -cfg, -c, -s): use a specified configuration file for this session. The path can be relative to the data folder.\b\fs28\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b0\fs24 --main-window (also: -mw): open the control window for Shield of Faith on startup, and not the other windows. Overrides config file settings.\b\fs28\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b0\fs24 --close-others (also: -co, -c): force closed other shield of faith instances and their associated shaderglass instances using their emergency feature. (It keeps track of processes to close using files in a hidden folder.)\b\fs28\par

